{"title_page": "Ioannis Christophides", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name            = Ioannis Christophides\n\n| office          = [[List of Ministers of Foreign Affairs of Cyprus|Ministrer of Foreign Affairs (Cyprus)]]\n| term_start      = 16 June 1972\n| term_end        = 8 \u039carch 1978\n| predecessor     = [[Spyros Kyprianou]]\n| successor       = [[Nicos A. Rolandis]]\n| president       = [[Makarios III]]\n\n| birth_date      = 21 January 1924\n| birth_place     = [[Nicosia Municipality]]\n| death_date      = {{Death date and age|2001|12|9|1924|01|21}}\n| death_place     =\n| nationality     = [[Greeks]]\n| citizenship     = [[Cyprus]]\n\n| spouse          = Marvel Christophide\n| children        = 2 daughters \n| education       = [[Jurisprudence]]\n| occupation      = [[Lawyer]]\n}}\n'''Ioannis Christophides''' ({{lang-el|\u0399\u03c9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2 \u03a7\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c6\u03af\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2}}; 21 January 1924-9 December 2001) was a [[Greek Cypriots|Cypriot]] politician who served as the [[List of Ministers of Foreign Affairs (Cyprus)|Minister of Foreign Affairs of Cyprus]] from June 1972 to March 1978.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.piopressreleases.com.cy/scans/6-1972_final%20outputs/jpegs/6-1972_0201.jpg|title=\u0399\u03c9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2 \u039a\u03bb. \u03a7\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c6\u03af\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2|last=|first=|date=1972-06-16|website=|publisher=[[Press and Information Office]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200402152912/https://www.piopressreleases.com.cy/scans/6-1972_final%20outputs/jpegs/6-1972_0201.jpg|language=el|archivedate=2020-04-02|accessdate=2020-04-02|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.polignosi.com/cgibin/hweb?-A=11224&-V=limmata|title=\u03a7\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c6\u03af\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0399\u03c9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2|last=|first=|date=|website=www.polignosi.com|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200402153714/http://www.polignosi.com/cgibin/hweb?-A=11224&-V=limmata|language=el|archivedate=2020-04-02|accessdate=2020-04-02|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stockwatch.com.cy/el/announcement/apeviose-o-proedros-toy-ds-tis-dome|title=\u0391\u03c0\u03b5\u03b2\u03af\u03c9\u03c3\u03b5 \u03bf \u03c0\u03c1\u03cc\u03b5\u03b4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c2 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u0394.\u03a3. \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 Dome|last=|first=|date=2001-12-12|website=|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200402153505/https://www.stockwatch.com.cy/el/announcement/apeviose-o-proedros-toy-ds-tis-dome|language=el|archivedate=2020-04-02|accessdate=2020-04-02|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hri.org/news/cyprus/kypegr/2001/01-12-09.kypegr.html#05|title=\u0391\u03c0\u03b5\u03b2\u03af\u03c9\u03c3\u03b5 \u03bf \u0399\u03c9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2 \u03a7\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c6\u03af\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2|last=|first=|date=2001-12-09|website=www.hri.org|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070326050116/http://www.hri.org/news/cyprus/kypegr/2001/01-12-09.kypegr.html#05|language=el|archivedate=2007-03-26|accessdate=2020-04-02|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.mfa.gov.cy/mfa/mfa2016.nsf/All/60154CCC785085E8C2257F9C00209D00?OpenDocument|title=Previous Ministers|last=|first=|date=|website=www.mfa.gov.cy|publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Cyprus)]]|language=|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190725011640/http://www.mfa.gov.cy/mfa/mfa2016.nsf/All/60154CCC785085E8C2257F9C00209D00?OpenDocument|archivedate=2019-07-25|accessdate=2019-07-25}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.cm.gov.cy/cm/cm.nsf/page33_gr/page33_gr?OpenDocument|title=\u039a\u03b1\u03c4\u03ac\u03bb\u03bf\u03b3\u03bf\u03c2 \u039f\u03bd\u03bf\u03bc\u03ac\u03c4\u03c9\u03bd \u03a5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03ce\u03bd \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03a5\u03c6\u03c5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03ce\u03bd \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0391\u03bd\u03b1\u03ba\u03ae\u03c1\u03c5\u03be\u03b7 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0394\u03b7\u03bc\u03bf\u03ba\u03c1\u03b1\u03c4\u03af\u03b1\u03c2.|last=|first=|date=|website=www.cm.gov.cy|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190727090009/http://www.cm.gov.cy/cm/cm.nsf/page33_gr/page33_gr?OpenDocument|language=el|archivedate=2019-07-27|accessdate=2019-07-27}}</ref> \n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Christofides}}\n[[Category:1924 births]]\n[[Category:2001 deaths]]\n[[Category:Cyprus Ministers of Foreign Affairs]]\n[[Category:Cypriot lawyers]]\n\n{{Cyprus-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name            = Ioannis Christophides\n\n| office          = [[List of Ministers of Foreign Affairs of Cyprus|Ministrer of Foreign Affairs (Cyprus)]]\n| term_start      = 16 June 1972\n| term_end        = 8 \u039carch 1978\n| predecessor     = [[Spyros Kyprianou]]\n| successor       = [[Nicos A. Rolandis]]\n| president       = [[Makarios III]]\n\n| birth_date      = 21 January 1924\n| birth_place     = [[Nicosia Municipality]]\n| death_date      = {{Death date and age|2001|12|9|1924|01|21}}\n| death_place     =\n| nationality     = [[Greeks]]\n| citizenship     = [[Cyprus]]\n\n| spouse          = Marvel Christophide\n| children        = 2 daughters \n| education       = [[Jurisprudence]]\n| occupation      = [[Lawyer]]\n}}\n'''Ioannis Christophides''' ({{lang-el|\u0399\u03c9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2 \u03a7\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c6\u03af\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2}}; 21 January 1924-9 December 2001) was a [[Greek Cypriots|Cypriot]] politician who served as the [[List of Ministers of Foreign Affairs (Cyprus)|Minister of Foreign Affairs of Cyprus]] from June 1972 to March 1978.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.piopressreleases.com.cy/scans/6-1972_final%20outputs/jpegs/6-1972_0201.jpg|title=\u0399\u03c9\u03ac\u03bd\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2 \u039a\u03bb. \u03a7\u03c1\u0